  "notes": [
    "Node math: 8 pods (user, project, task, api, api-gateway, postgresql, mysql, mongo) * ~512Mi baseline request = 4096Mi total pod memory. 4x t3.small nodes (1.4GiB allocatable each) yield 5.6GiB total, safely satisfying the application requests plus AWS/K8s daemonsets.",
    "Storage & State: Kompose extracted PVCs for mongo, mysql, and postgresql but bare Pods. In Kubernetes, stateful database components should use StatefulSets with VolumeClaimTemplates rather than static PVCs and Pods.",
    "EBS CSI Add-on: Since the databases require PersistentVolumeClaims, the `aws-ebs-csi-driver` EKS add-on is mandatory. A default StorageClass backed by the CSI driver must also be created so PVCs provision correctly.",
    "Ingress: The api-gateway service (port 9090) will be exposed externally using an AWS Application Load Balancer via the AWS Load Balancer Controller. HTTP-only setup is sufficient for initial validation tests.",
    "Kompose Discrepancies: Kompose converted Compose services to raw 'Pod' resources with 'restartPolicy: Never'. These must be upgraded to 'Deployment' resources (for stateless apps) and 'StatefulSet' resources (for databases) to ensure reliability and self-healing.",
    "NAT Gateway is required because nodes will be placed in private subnets and must download container images from public registries (Docker Hub)."
  ]
}
